nts & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "farm security administration/office of war information black-and-white negatives", "catalog", "prints and photographs division", "american memory"], "score": 24.512396, "shelf_id": "LC-USF34- 065043-D [P&P]", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["united states", "montana", "safety film negatives", "helena", "lewis and clark county"], "timestamp": "2022-04-26T01:00:18.218Z", "title": "Helena, Montana. Demolition of buildings damaged in 1935 earthquakes", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017814572/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01/data/sn86075189/00414211057/1958042501/0088.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mthi:batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01:data:sn86075189:00414211057:1958042501:0082/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01/data/sn86075189/00414211057/1958042501/0088.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86075189/1958-04-25/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01/data/sn86075189/00414211057/1958042501/0088.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mthi:batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01:data:sn86075189:00414211057:1958042501:0082/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01/data/sn86075189/00414211057/1958042501/0088.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86075189/1958-04-25/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_douglasfir_ver01/data/sn86075189/00414211057/1958042501/0088.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86075189/1958-04-25/ed-1/?sp=7"], "batch": ["mthi_douglasfir_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/montana/", "2/united states/montana/lewis and clark/", "3/united states/montana/lewis and clark/helena/"], "contributor": ["montana historical society; helena, mt"], "date": "1958-04-25", "dates": ["1958-04-25"], "description": ["The Eisenhower Tragedy Continued From Page Six 1957 while the Russians were prepar ing to launch their first Sputnik Though Dulles and Humphrey were dividing policy between themthe formers policy abroad often undercut by the latters economy at homethe president recovered satisfactorily from his first illness seemed to be grasping again the tangled reigns of power and was in his best form by the early summer of 1956 On June 9 he suffered his second illness But he recovered from a serious operation so rapidly that he decided to seek a second term HIS GREATEST MISTAKE That was his greatest mistake and assured his ultimate tragedy It should be remembered however that he did not foresee the third illness In addi tion he was persuaded to run both by Republicans who considered him es sential to the nation and those who only wished to ride on his coattails while privately abhorring his philoso phy Eisenhower was easily reelected but lost control of the legislature Still the president appeared to be a well man and a regnant leader until the summer of 1957 Then four events engulfed him The first of itself was sufficient to wreck his leadership A paralytic stroke"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-07-03T13:45:52.190Z", "group": ["ndnp/mthi", "montana-historical-society-helena-mt-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86075189/1958-04-25/ed-1/?sp=7", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.